metadata.name: ARTEFACT - 09792 #1/22
metadata.description:
ARTEFACTS - A Generative Glitch Series 

Artefacting can be described as a visible or audible anomaly created during the processing or transmission of digital data. Each Artefact is an oddity, glitch, or distortion created through the lens of a virtual camera observing procedurally generated graphics.

Collectors will have the option of receiving a high resolution png or physical archival print.

ARTEFACT - 09792 | 4320 x 7680 px | PNG |
